Package xxl.core.pipes.sinks

Interface Summary
Sink<I> The framework for query processing is based on dataflow graphs, therefore it consists of three fundamental types of components: sources, operators and sinks.
SinkMetaDataManagement  
SinkMetaDataManagement.ContainsSinkMetaDataDependencies  
 

Class Summary
AbstractSink<I> Superclass for each kind of terminal sinks in a query graph.
AbstractSink.SinkMetaDataDependenciesContainer Container for the meta data dependencies.
AbstractTemporalSink<I> Superclass for sinks that receive instances of TemporalObject, i.e., the transferred elements consist of a value and a time interval.
AbstractTimeStampSink<I,I2 extends TimeStampedObject<I>> Superclass for sinks that receive TimeStampedObjects, i.e., the received elements consist of a value and a time stamp.
DevNull<I> Sink that discards all elements without further processing.
PNAbstractSink<I>  
Printer<I> Sink component in a query graph that prints the elements streaming in to a user-defined PrintStream.
SinkCursor<I> Sink component in a query graph that provides an iteration over the elements streaming in.
Tester<I> Sink component in a query graph that is usally used for test purposes.
VisualSink<I> Sink component in a query graph that provides a simple graphical user interface (GUI).
 

Exception Summary
SinkIsDoneException This exception is thrown to indicate that a sink has already stopped processing, because it will not receive further elements.
